Database Management System (DBMS)
1. DBMS kya hai aur iska primary function?
DBMS ek software hai jo data ko efficiently store, manage aur retrieve karne me madad karta hai. Iske main functions hain:

Data storage and retrieval
Multi-user access
Security aur backup management
2. DBMS vs Traditional File System (3 advantages)
Data Redundancy kam hoti hai: Same data multiple files me store nahi hota.
Better security: Authentication aur authorization provide karta hai.
Concurrent access: Multiple users ek saath data access kar sakte hain bina kisi issue ke.
3. DBMS ke main types aur examples
Hierarchical DBMS: IBM IMS
Network DBMS: IDS (Integrated Data Store)
Relational DBMS (RDBMS): MySQL, PostgreSQL
NoSQL DBMS: MongoDB, Cassandra
4. DBMS me data security aur integrity ka role?
DBMS access control, encryption aur authentication provide karta hai jo data ko unauthorized access se bachata hai.

5. DBMS concurrent user access kaise handle karta hai?
DBMS locking mechanisms aur transactions ka use karta hai jisse ek hi data ko multiple users efficiently access kar sakein.

DBMS Architecture
1. Three-layer DBMS architecture kya hai?
Physical Level: Data ka actual storage format.
Logical Level: Data structure aur relationships define karta hai.
View Level: Users ke liye customized views create karta hai.
2. Physical, Logical aur View levels me difference?
Physical level: Hard disk ya cloud me data kaise store ho raha hai.
Logical level: Tables, relationships aur constraints define karta hai.
View level: Users ko sirf unka relevant data dikhata hai.
3. Modular architecture ka importance?
Modular design system ko flexible aur scalable banata hai.

4. Three-schema architecture ka example?
Ek banking system me:

Physical level: Transactions hard drive/cloud me stored hoti hain.
Logical level: Accounts, transactions aur customer tables maintain hoti hain.
View level: Customer ko sirf uske account details dikhai deti hain.
5. User aur DBMS ke beech communication flow?
User → Application → DBMS (Query Processing) → Database → Response back to User

Data Independence
1. Data Independence kya hai aur iska significance?
Data independence ka matlab hai ki users aur applications bina kisi major change ke database structure me modifications kar sakein.

2. Logical vs Physical Data Independence?
Physical Data Independence: Storage structure change ho to bhi logical structure impact nahi hota.
Logical Data Independence: Tables ya relationships me changes se applications affect nahi hoti.
3. Data Independence application scalability kaise improve karta hai?
Storage ya logical changes easily handle kiye ja sakte hain, bina downtime ke.

4. Real-world scenario?
Agar ek e-commerce company apna data SQL se NoSQL me migrate kare to bhi user-facing applications bina issue ke kaam karein.

5. Legacy systems me Data Independence achieve karna mushkil kyu hai?
Old systems tightly coupled hote hain, jisme data aur application code interconnected hota hai.

File System vs DBMS
1. File System vs DBMS (5 Differences)
Feature	File System	DBMS
Data Redundancy	High	Low
Security	Limited	Advanced
Data Consistency	Low	High
Multi-user Access	Difficult	Efficient
Query Optimization	No	Yes
2. Large-scale data management ke liye DBMS better kyu hai?
DBMS efficient indexing, multi-user access aur data integrity ensure karta hai jo large-scale applications ke liye zaroori hai.

3. DBMS data redundancy kaise kam karta hai?
Normalization techniques ka use karke duplicate data ko eliminate karta hai.

4. File System vs DBMS me security differences?
File system me password protection basic hoti hai.
DBMS me role-based access control, encryption aur audit logs available hote hain.
5. Indexing ka role aur DBMS vs File-based storage?
DBMS indexing se faster search operations karta hai.
File-based storage me direct searching slow hoti hai.
